                <note rend="inline" type="source">354.116 M 81/1: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="30" xml:id="d193fn30">See last paragraph for instructions
                        to repeat to The Hague, Copenhagen, Christiania, and Berne.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-05T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1921—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department advised that British diplomatic and consular officers here refuse
                    visas to American Mormon missionaries going to South Africa. Investigate and
                    report.</p>
                <p>Repeat <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi> to The Hague, Copenhagen,
                    Christiania, and Berne.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
